properties.Name: IdentificationComponent

Columns.Name: IdentificationId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of the identification.

Columns.Name: ComponentId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of the Component.

Columns.Name: IdentificationComponentInstalledTimestamp
Columns.Description: The timestamp the badge component was installed in the identification.

Columns.Name: IdentificationComponentRemovedTimestamp
Columns.Description: The timestamp the badge component was removed from the identification.

Columns.Name: IdentificationComponentNote
Columns.Description: A note, comment or additional information regarding the identification component.

Columns.Name: IdentificationComponentTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Identification Component Type.

Columns.Name: IrTagId
Columns.Description:
The unique identifier of an IR Tag.

The transmitter/receiver pair or transceiver plus the information storage mechanism attached to the object is referred to as the tag, transponder, electronic label, code plate and various other terms. 

Although transponder is technically the most accurate, the most common term and the one preferred by the Automatic Identification Manufacturers is tag.

Columns.Name: RfidTagId
Columns.Description:
The unique identifier of a RFID Tag.

The transmitter/receiver pair or transceiver plus the information storage mechanism attached to the object is referred to as the tag, transponder, electronic label, code plate and various other terms. 

Although transponder is technically the most accurate, the most common term and the one preferred by the Automatic Identification Manufacturers is tag.

Columns.Name: BarCodeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Bar Code.

Columns.Name: RadiationDetectionDeviceId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Radiation Detection Device.

Columns.Name: PhotographId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a photograph.
